“A player on the batting team scores a run by touching all the bases in sequence, ending at home plate.”
Does he get to bat again? or he has to leave and the next batter faces the pitcher?





Raymond Chen Author
July 18, 2019


  0  Collapse this comment
Copy link
The batters take their turn in the declared batting order. Once the batter hits a fair ball (or strikes out or is awarded a base), the batting phase is over.




