"An inning is completed when each team has had a turn at bat and a turn in the field."
That is not correct.  A half-inning is completed when the team who is on offense that half-inning has three OUTS recorded against it.  Two half-innings make one inning.  :-) 
Your text makes it sound like all players from one team get to bat.
